definitions.definition: A struggle or contest ; conflict ; especially between the protagonist and antagonist in a literary work.
An intellectual conflict or apparent competition of ideas .
A contest in ancient Greece , as in athletics or music , in which prizes were awarded.
A two-player board game played on a hexagonally-tiled board, popular in Victorian times.

main_definition: ( countable ) A struggle or contest ; conflict ; especially between the protagonist and antagonist in a literary work.
